flowchart LR
    A[Decision and causal question] --> B[Theory of change and protocol]
    B --> C[Eligibility, assignment, treatment, and metrics]
    C --> D[Readiness, power, privacy, and rollback review]
    D --> E[Assignment]
    E --> F[Observed treatment exposure]
    F --> G[Guardrail and data-quality monitoring]
    G --> H[Predeclared analysis]
    H --> I{Decision}
    I -->|Adopt| J[Bounded rollout]
    I -->|Modify| B
    I -->|Extend| F
    I -->|Reject or reverse| K[Stop and preserve negative result]
    J --> L[Long-term follow-up and replication]
    K --> L
    L --> A

    Q[Versioned evidence, provenance, external factors, and decision records] -. applies throughout .-> B
    Q -. applies throughout .-> F
    Q -. applies throughout .-> H
    Q -. applies throughout .-> L
